        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 1:51PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 151 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Headrick, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Snyder, Mountain Park, Indiahoma, Headrick, Tom Steed Reservoir,
southwestern Fort Sill, and southwestern Wichita Mountains Wildlife
Refuge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
